modules.description: Calculates the memory footprint of OCaml values, including nested structures and polymorphic variants. It operates on arbitrary OCaml types, such as lists, arrays, and custom record types. Used to diagnose memory usage in performance-critical applications or when optimizing data representation.

Computes memory usage of OCaml heap values by traversing their runtime representation, supporting depth-limited analysis and root-based heap inspection. Operates on custom types like `info` and `tag_info`, which encapsulate detailed memory metrics and tag-specific breakdowns. Calculates byte sizes, compares memory differences between snapshots, and generates human-readable reports with tag mappings.
